http://schema.org/creator.name: creator
http://schema.org/creator.desc: The creator/author of this CreativeWork. This is the same as the Author property for CreativeWork.

http://schema.org/about.name: about
http://schema.org/about.desc: The subject matter of the content.

http://schema.org/character.name: character
http://schema.org/character.desc: Fictional person connected with a creative work.

http://schema.org/subEvent.name: sub event
http://schema.org/subEvent.desc: An Event that is part of this event. For example, a conference event includes many presentations, each of which is a subEvent of the conference.

http://schema.org/productionCompany.name: production company
http://schema.org/productionCompany.desc: The production company or studio responsible for the item e.g. series, video game, episode etc.

http://schema.org/partOfSeason.name: part of season
http://schema.org/partOfSeason.desc: The season to which this episode belongs.

http://schema.org/birthPlace.name: birth place
http://schema.org/birthPlace.desc: The place where the person was born.

http://schema.org/genre.name: genre
http://schema.org/genre.desc: Genre of the creative work, broadcast channel or group.

http://schema.org/founder.name: founder
http://schema.org/founder.desc: A person who founded this organization.

http://schema.org/givenName.name: given name
http://schema.org/givenName.desc: Given name. In the U.S., the first name of a Person.

http://schema.org/memberOf.name: member of
http://schema.org/memberOf.desc: An Organization (or ProgramMembership) to which this Person or Organization belongs.

http://schema.org/honorificPrefix.name: honorific prefix
http://schema.org/honorificPrefix.desc: An honorific prefix preceding a Person's name such as Dr/Mrs/Mr.

http://schema.org/award.name: award
http://schema.org/award.desc: An award won by or for this item.

http://schema.org/foundingLocation.name: founding location
http://schema.org/foundingLocation.desc: The place where the Organization was founded.

http://schema.org/parentOrganization.name: parent organization
http://schema.org/parentOrganization.desc: The larger organization that this organization is a subOrganization of, if any.

http://schema.org/inLanguage.name: in language
http://schema.org/inLanguage.desc: The language of the content or performance or used in an action. Please use one of the language codes from the IETF BCP 47 standard. See also availableLanguage.

http://schema.org/actor.name: actor
http://schema.org/actor.desc: An actor, e.g. in tv, radio, movie, video games etc., or in an event. Actors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

http://schema.org/superEvent.name: super event
http://schema.org/superEvent.desc: An event that this event is a part of. For example, a collection of individual music performances might each have a music festival as their superEvent.

http://schema.org/competitor.name: competitor
http://schema.org/competitor.desc: A competitor in a sports event.

http://schema.org/deathPlace.name: death place
http://schema.org/deathPlace.desc: The place where the person died.

http://schema.org/containedInPlace.name: contained in place
http://schema.org/containedInPlace.desc: The basic containment relation between a place and one that contains it.

http://schema.org/subOrganization.name: sub organization
http://schema.org/subOrganization.desc: A relationship between two organizations where the first includes the second, e.g., as a subsidiary. See also: the more specific 'department' property.

http://schema.org/author.name: author
http://schema.org/author.desc: The author of this content or rating. Please note that author is special in that HTML 5 provides a special mechanism for indicating authorship via the rel tag. That is equivalent to this and may be used interchangeably.

http://schema.org/copyrightHolder.name: copyright holder
http://schema.org/copyrightHolder.desc: The party holding the legal copyright to the CreativeWork.

http://schema.org/hasOccupation.name: has occupation
http://schema.org/hasOccupation.desc: The Person's occupation. For past professions, use Role for expressing dates.

http://schema.org/alumniOf.name: alumni of
http://schema.org/alumniOf.desc: An organization that the person is an alumni of.

http://schema.org/partOfSeries.name: part of series
http://schema.org/partOfSeries.desc: The series to which this episode or season belongs.

http://schema.org/director.name: director
http://schema.org/director.desc: A director of e.g. tv, radio, movie, video gaming etc. content, or of an event. Directors can be associated with individual items or with a series, episode, clip.

http://schema.org/isBasedOn.name: is based on
http://schema.org/isBasedOn.desc: A resource from which this work is derived or from which it is a modification or adaption.

http://schema.org/producer.name: producer
http://schema.org/producer.desc: The person or organization who produced the work (e.g. music album, movie, tv/radio series etc.).

http://schema.org/isPartOf.name: is part of
http://schema.org/isPartOf.desc: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense), is part of.

http://schema.org/hasPart.name: has part
http://schema.org/hasPart.desc: Indicates an item or CreativeWork that is part of this item, or CreativeWork (in some sense).

http://schema.org/homeLocation.name: home location
http://schema.org/homeLocation.desc: A contact location for a person's residence.

http://bioschemas.org/bioChemInteraction.name: bio chem interaction
http://bioschemas.org/bioChemInteraction.desc: This term is proposed for full integration into Schema.org, pending implementation feedback and adoption from applications and websites.

http://schema.org/countryOfOrigin.name: country of origin
http://schema.org/countryOfOrigin.desc: The country of origin of something, including products as well as creative works such as movie and TV content.

http://schema.org/containsPlace.name: contains place
http://schema.org/containsPlace.desc: The basic containment relation between a place and another that it contains.

http://schema.org/contentLocation.name: content location
http://schema.org/contentLocation.desc: The location depicted or described in the content. For example, the location in a photograph or painting.

http://schema.org/familyName.name: family name
http://schema.org/familyName.desc: Family name. In the U.S., the last name of a Person.

http://schema.org/location.name: location
http://schema.org/location.desc: The location of, for example, where an event is happening, where an organization is located, or where an action takes place.

http://schema.org/knowsLanguage.name: knows language
http://schema.org/knowsLanguage.desc: This term is proposed for full integration into Schema.org, pending implementation feedback and adoption from applications and websites.
